    "Similarly, the 3-OPT entails the removal of three inferior edges and the addition of three superior edges. 50 Fig.",
    "1 A TSP instance with 50 nodes (TSP) Fig. 2 2-OPT and 3-OPT heuristics for TSP [41] The search capability of 3-OPT surpasses that of 2-OPT, increasing the likelihood of discovering superior solutions.",
    "However, the implementation complexity of 3-OPT outweighs that of 2-OPT [38,42].",
    "The primary difference between 3-OPT and 2-OPT lies in the difficulty of reconnecting remaining segments.",
    "3-OPT presents a higher reconnection difficulty compared to 2-OPT, because 3-OPT offers up to seven different reconnection types [41], whereas 2-OPT only has one reconnection type.The Lin-Kernighan-Helsgaun (LKH) algorithm [43][44][45] (LKH, LKH-2, LKH-3) are typical heuristic algorithms capable of effectively solving routing problems, including TSP.Heuristic algorithms typically find high-quality approximate solutions quickly."
